Package: metavirus
Title: metavirus: an public api and integrative tool to get viruses data into R system
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Amanda",family = "Andrade", role = c("cre", "aut"), email = "aandradebio@gmail.com"),
   	person(given = "Otavio",family = "Brustolini", role= "aut"),
   	person(given = "Eduardo",family = "Wagner", role= "aut"),
	person(given = "Ana",family = "Vasconcelos",role = c("aut", "ths")))
Description: metavirus aims to combine the three major virus data repositories (VirusHost, ViralZone and NCBI Refseq) into a R package for facilitating the application of the viruses descriptions, variants sequences and taxonomy data into the statistical environment of R. It is also developing a public api to explore the data integration mechanisms with phylogenetic, metagenome or machine learning approach.
